         Reegor: I understand you totally, but making ANY zone more popular is better for everyone because other zones will then become less frequented and have less competition.  If PoM became more popular, sebilis/Velk will see less action.  Back before the Velk/Chardok/CT revamp seb had like 50+ people regularly.  Now on my server about ~20 people are there - sadly an AE group usually - but it allows me alot more room to solo and group.  I do agree with you on the "unfun" part, though, but I think a zone can be fun and popular at the same time - take Chardok, for instance, or HS.</P><P></P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
