        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I don't agree with making lguk like CT - I just hate zones where you must BYOG because the mobs are so damn hard that only a balanced and uber group can fight at the places they want.  I enjoy pick-up groups and "ghetto" groups because there necros can really shine, and of course I enjoy soloing because, after all, I'm a necro.</P><P>If they revamp lguk I hope they make it so that the starting mobs are in the low 40's and then move on from there, ending with the top bosses being in the high 50's and maybe level 60.  I'd like it if they kept the undead population, or increased it like they did with <BR>Chardok.  Call it a take-over by the ghouls.  The mobs definitely should NOT be hitting in the 200's - I'd love it if the mobs start off hitting in the 90's and then moves on for a max of 180, with the boss hitting for 200-300.  That has always been the aspect of Lguk I loved - the smooth flow and transition from lower level to higher level mobs that allows the zone to support all kinds of players, instead of just one kind like CT.</P><P>Personally, though, I wouldn't touch Lguk - Lguk is one of the top zones for paladin/cleric/necro soloing and power leveling.  Seeing as how Vi wants to concentrate on the high-end game, having a dungeon where people can get to the 50's fast is actually quite a good idea.  I mean, aside from Lguk, what's there on the old world that'll allow you to move from the 40's to the 50's? The ever so crowded Solusek B, which is like 1/4th the size of Lguk if we're not counting the efreeti/FGs which aren't 40-50 expable?</P><P></P><P>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
